Ashwagandha

Withania somnifera

Medicinal Plants
Author: Mir et al.
Published: 10/08/2021
Read Time: 3 minute
Category: Medicinal Plants
Location: India

Description

Ashwagandha (Withania somnifera) contains a rich variety of chemical compounds responsible for its medicinal properties. The primary bioactive constituents are withanolides, which are steroidal lactones, including compounds like withaferin A, withanolide A, and withanolide D. These compounds structurally resemble the ginsenosides found in Panax ginseng, earning Ashwagandha the nickname "Indian ginseng"

The mineral content includes essential elements like copper, iron, zinc, magnesium, manganese, cobalt, and nickel, which also support its health benefits .

This detailed phytochemical content explains its wide use in traditional Indian medicine and growing scientific validation.


Medicinal Properties

Antiseptic anti-inflammatory adaptogenic immunomodulatory neuroprotective antitumor aphrodisiac antioxidant analgesic antistress antibacterial antipyretic

Common Uses

  • 1)Root powder or extract used as a general tonic
  • 2(Leaf paste applied for inflammation and skin infections
  • 3)Leaf juice used for conjunctivitis
  • 4)Bark decoction for asthma and bed sores
  • 4)Herbal teas, syrups, and tablets prepared from roots and extracts
